=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is a cheap horse worth it just to med standing?</span><hr size=1> I have a horse for my cleric, and it works wonders for her mana when grouped outdoors, but I personally would not put my mage on one.  Eventhough pets behave differently now, it's inbedded in my mind the need to pay close attention and see every move my pet makes, just incase he gets out of line.  Unfortunately, on a horse your view is partially obstructed, and maneuvering around isn't the same.  Whether or not you wish to buy a horse just for the mana efficiency is entirely up to you, as was said above. <p><img src=http://home.sc.rr.com/kimmisc/TelVol.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usnowowlwhitemoon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Snowowl Whitemoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#333333>(7/16/02 4:51:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=845.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is a cheap horse worth it just to med standing?</span><hr size=1> It isn't so much mana efficient as it is a aggro reducer for sitting down after having the pet attack or casting a damage spell.  So there is that also to consider. <p><center>All that is gold does not glitter,<br>
