I'm certainly not a rich mage but at lvl 25 or so I told myself &quot;I wanna horsie!!!&quot; so I more or less put everything else behind for this goal.<br>
At lvl 44 I was finally be able to afford one (still having Raw Silk in some slots aso ;-) )<br>
And when I got it I never regretted that decision.<br>
<br>
Of course, that's mainly because it supports my current &quot;playing style&quot;. I like being in outdoor zones with many MOBs around. (Dawnshroud around 45, then echo caverns (horse useless ;-) ) and since lvl 49 in DL)<br>
I usually pull a MOB to my Pet, summon my horse and then nuke from there.<br>
<br>
And I definately LOVE it. <br>
I hardly ever get aggro by the MOBs anymore and my mana pool is also very fine.<br>
when the fight is over I click horse off and look for a new MOB (have JBoots as well).<br>
<br>
Anyway: I think it was the best investment I could do.<br>
If I look at items you can get for about 8k on my sever I have to say that the horse is definately worth its money.<br>
<br>
As for the sight. Sometimes it just doesnt disturb me if I dont see much (like when I only summon the horse for the duration of the fight). If I need to stay longer on the horse then I usually switch to &quot;overhead view&quot; and change the angle a bit and I have a great view as well.<br>
Or...if the terrain allows it I try to position myself at &quot;downhill place&quot; because then I hardly see the head of the horse anymore.<br>
